CT"/> A large portion of CEFC's assets is concentrated in overseas markets.<ref name="WCT"/> Since 2013 the company has been listed on the [[Fortune Global 500]] list.<ref>[http://fortune.com/global500/cefc-china-energy-342/ Fortune Global 500]</ref> It rose from a rank of 342 in 2015 to 229 in June 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.southmoney.com/yinhang/lccp/201607/641996.html|title=2016年财富世界500强最新排行榜名单 财富世界500强中国110家上榜-理财产品 - 南方财富网|website=www.southmoney.com|access-date=2016-07-24}}</ref> Most of the company is owned by Shanghai Energy Fund Investment Ltd (SEFI), which is registered under [[Ye Jianming]], the chairman of CEFC.<ref name="WCT"/> Czech President [[Miloš Zeman]] has appointed CEFC's founder Ye Jianming as his economic adviser.<ref>"[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cefc-china/chinas-cefc-has-big-ambitions-but-little-known-about-ownership-funding-idUSKBN14X0B5 China’s CEFC has big ambitions, but little known about ownership, funding]". Reuters. 13 January 2017.</ref> The company is linked to the [[People's Liberation Army]].<ref>"[https://www.ft.com/content/e3f8cbd2-983f-11e7-a652-cde3f882dd7b Opaque Chinese oil group makes clear gains in former Soviet bloc]". ''Financial Times''. 13 September 2017.</ref><ref>"[http://www.scmp.com/business/companies/article/2072726/whos-39-year-old-paying-hk14-billion-three-office-floors Who’s that 39-year-old paying HK$1.4 billion for three office floors?]". ''South China Morning Post''. 21 February 2017.</ref>
