{{citation style|date=October 2010}} {{Infobox film | name = Journey to the End of Coal | image = | director = Samuel Bollendorff and Abel Ségrétin | producer = Arnaud Dressen ([[Honkytonk Films]]) | narrator = | music = | editing = | sound mix = | distributor = [[Le Monde|lemonde.fr]] / with the support of [[National Center of Cinematography and the moving image|CNC]] and the SCAM in partnership with [[Amnesty International]] / [[Reporters Without Borders]] | released = {{Film date|2008}} | runtime = | country = France | language = french, english }}
'''Journey to the End of Coal''' is a French [[web documentary]] directed by Samuel Bollendorff<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.francophonie-texas.org/journey-to-the-end-of-coal/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-10-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726063410/http://www.francophonie-texas.org/journey-to-the-end-of-coal/ |archivedate=2011-07-26 |df= }}</ref> and Abel Segretin.
Based on the ''[[choose your own adventure]]'' principle, the interactive documentary tells the story of millions of Chinese coal miners who are risking their lives to satisfy their country’s appetite for economic growth.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.interactivedocumentary.net/2008/09/16/journey-to-the-end-of-coal/ | title=Journey to the End of Coal .:. Interactive Documentary}}</ref>
