{{British Indian units of mass}}
A '''passeree''' is an obsolete unit of mass used in [[Bengal]] that approximately equalled 4.677 &nbsp;kg (10.3&nbsp;lb). Five [[seer (unit)|seers]] made up one passeree. After [[Metrication in India|metrication]] in the mid-20th century, the unit became obsolete.

