{{Infobox company |name = Slovenské energetické strojárne |logo = |caption = |type = private |genre = |fate = |predecessor = |successor = |foundation = |founder = |defunct = |location_city = [[Tlmače]] |location_country = [[Slovakia]] |location = |locations = |area_served = |key_people = |industry = [[Power engineering]], [[Energy]], [[Mechanical engineering]] |products = boilers, power engineering equipment |production = |services = development, design, manufacture, assembly, commissioning |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |aum = |assets = |equity = |num_employees = 1873 - 31 December 2010 |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |homepage = [http://www.ses.sk www.ses.sk] |footnotes = |intl = }}
'''Slovenské energetické strojárne a.s. (SES Tlmače)''' ({{lang-en|Slovak Energy Machines}}) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] joint-stock company primarily engaged in the design, manufacture and assembly of power engineering equipment.<ref name=SME1>{{cite news|title=SES Tlmače boli v prvom polroku v červených číslach (SES Tlmače numbers were in the red during the first half of the year)|url=http://ekonomika.sme.sk/c/6057890/ses-tlmace-boli-v-prvom-polroku-v-cervenych-cislach.html|accessdate=29 May 2012|newspaper=SME|date=16 September 2011}}</ref> It is headquartered in the Slovak city [[Tlmače]]. As of 2012 the company is in the process of merging into the EP Industries holding owned by the Slovak investment company [[J&T]] and [[Czech people|Czech]] billionaire [[Daniel Křetínský]].<ref name=HN1>{{cite news|title=J&T rieši problém. V SES Tlmače prepustia tristo ľudí (J&T is solving a problem. SES Tlmače will lay off 300 people)|url=http://hnonline.sk/c1-55911040-j-t-riesi-problem-ses-tlmace-prepustia-stovky-ludi|accessdate=29 May 2012|newspaper=Hospodárske Noviny|date=24 May 2012}}</ref>
== Description == The Company provides boilers for combustion of coal, oil, gas and biomass and determined for thermal power plants or combined heating and power plants as well as incinerating plants. In addition to equipment for power engineering, the slovenske energeticke strojarne, gas, metallurgy and consumer goods industry. It also provides services in power engineering: development, designing, manufacture, assembly and commissioning. Its products are divided in five segments: power plants; boilers; condensers, heat exchangers and pipelines; steel constructions and other equipment.
It is operational through a number of subsidiaries, including SES Hungaria Kft., based in Hungary, SES Bohemia sro, based in the Czech Republic, and SES Chile, based in Chile, among others.
== History == The company was founded in the 1950s in [[Czechoslovakia]]. It was transformed into a joint-stock company in 1992. Since August 2006, the majority shareholder of SES Tlmače is a [[Cyprus|Cypriot]] company Segfield Investment, part of the [[J&T]] Group, one of two biggest investment companies in [[Slovakia]].<ref name="SME1" /> In May 2012, the company announced its plan to lay off 300 employees.<ref name="HN1" />
