'''Wharetutu Te Aroha Stirling''' (28 January 1924 &ndash; 31 March 1993) was a notable New Zealand tribal leader and conservationist. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, she identified with the [[Ngāi Tahu]] [[iwi]]. She was born in [[Lyttelton, New Zealand|Lyttelton]], [[North Canterbury]], [[New Zealand]] in 1924.<ref name="DNZB Stirling">{{DNZB|title=Wharetutu Te Aroha Stirling|first=Tipene|last=O'Regan|id=5s47|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

